# Component Rules

## Component Structure

### Standard Component Template
```javascript
/**
 * @version 0.0.1
 * Updated On : [Date]
 * Component description
 */
import { useState } from 'react';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';

const ComponentName = ({ prop1, prop2 = defaultValue }) => {
  //-------------- State & Variables --------------//
  const [state, setState] = useState();
  
  //-------------- Hooks --------------//
  // Custom hooks, Redux hooks, etc.
  
  //-------------- Effects --------------//
  // useEffect, etc.
  
  //-------------- Event Handlers --------------//
  const handleAction = () => {
    // Handler logic
  };
  
  //-------------- Render --------------//
  return (
    <div className="...">
      {/* Component JSX */}
    </div>
  );
};

export default ComponentName;
```

## shadcn/ui Components

### Import Pattern
```javascript
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '@/components/ui/card';
import { Input } from '@/components/ui/input';
```

### Component Usage
- Always use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui`
- Use proper variants and sizes: `<Button variant="outline" size="sm">`
- Follow shadcn component patterns and props

### Extending Components
- If modifying shadcn components, do so in `src/components/ui/[component].jsx`
- Maintain backward compatibility with shadcn updates
- Use `cn()` utility for className merging

## Tailwind CSS

### Class Organization
- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively
- Group related classes: `flex items-center justify-between`
- Use responsive prefixes: `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Use dark mode: `dark:bg-background`

### Common Patterns
```javascript
// Container
className="bg-background min-h-screen p-4"

// Card
className="rounded-lg border bg-card p-6 shadow-sm"

// Flex layouts
className="flex items-center justify-between gap-4"

// Text
className="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight"
className="text-muted-foreground text-sm"

// Spacing
className="space-y-4" // Vertical spacing
className="gap-4" // Flex/Grid gap
```

### Theme Variables
- Use CSS variables for theming: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`
- Use semantic colors: `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-destructive`
- Support dark mode with `dark:` prefix

## Component Organization

### File Structure
```
src/components/
  ComponentName/
    index.jsx          # Main component
    components/        # Sub-components (if needed)
    hooks/             # Component-specific hooks (if needed)
```

### Component Exports
- Export default for main component
- Use named exports for sub-components if needed
- Export from `src/components/index.js` for easy imports

### Props Interface
- Use descriptive prop names
- Provide default values where appropriate
- Document props with JSDoc for complex components
- Use PropTypes or TypeScript if available

## Reusable Components

### Creating Reusable Components
```javascript
/**
 * Reusable component description
 * @param {Array} items - Array of items to display
 * @param {Function} onSelect - Callback when item is selected
 * @param {boolean} disabled - Whether component is disabled
 */
export const ReusableComponent = ({ 
  items = [], 
  onSelect, 
  disabled = false 
}) => {
  // Implementation
};
```

### Component Composition
- Prefer composition over configuration
- Use children prop for flexible layouts
- Create wrapper components for common patterns

## Performance

### Optimization
- Use `React.memo()` for expensive components
- Memoize callbacks with `useCallback()`
- Memoize computed values with `useMemo()`
- Lazy load heavy components

### Best Practices
- Keep components small and focused
- Extract logic into custom hooks
- Avoid inline object/array creation in render
- Use proper keys for lists

## Accessibility

### ARIA Attributes
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Add `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
- Use `sr-only` class for screen reader text
- Ensure keyboard navigation works

### Examples
```javascript
<Button aria-label="Close dialog">
  <X className="h-4 w-4" />
  <span className="sr-only">Close</span>
</Button>
```
